-- Spain's BFA sells full 2.99 pct in Mapfre for 276.8 mln euros
-- By Elisabeth O'Leary
-- Tue Sep 23, 2014 02:54AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, Sept 23 (Reuters) - Spain's Banco Financiero y de Ahorros (BFA), the state-owned holding company which controls Bankia <BKIA.MC>, said on Tuesday it had sold its entire 2.99 percent stake in insurer Mapfre <MAP.MC> for 276.8 million euros (355.58 million US dollar).

